Unsurprisingly, Mussolini has triumphed once again. The organisation has however, surprisingly turned from left-wing politics, instead exalting the existing institutions, seemingly becoming a new reactionary force in response to us.

- @root: Opportunists.

@council_1920
on-arrival: pnf_leader = "Grand Council"; veterans_pnf -= 5;

With Mussolini absent, the Grand Council of Fascism, comprised of Cesare Forni, Dino Grandi, Emilio De Bono and prominent members of the Fasci have formed to control the organisation, with Mussolini *de jure* operating in absentia.

Regardless, the lack of leadership seems to have weakened the organisation, even if only slightly.